.START 

Three air carriers were selected to provide the first scheduled all-cargo service between the U.S. and Mexico, the Transportation Department said. 

United Parcel Service will serve Mexico City, Guadalajara and Monterrey from Houston.
Federal Express will serve the same locations from Harlingen, Texas.
Evergreen International will serve Mexico City from McAllen, Texas, and Miami.
The carriers are authorized to begin service Oct. 23. 

